modules.description: Establishes a WebSocket connection and returns reader and writer functions for frame-based communication. Processes JSON queries and transactions, returning results or specific error states. Handles message status tracking and validation for incoming responses.

Provides functions to construct and execute Gremlin queries, serialize and deserialize graph data, and manage connections to graph databases. Works with custom query builders, JSON-encoded results, and protocol buffers for data exchange. Used to interact with graph databases like JanusGraph or Amazon Neptune through a low-level, protocol-driven interface.

Establishes a WebSocket connection for frame-based communication, providing reader and writer functions that process JSON queries and transactions, with support for error handling and response validation. Tracks message status and ensures data integrity during transmission. Supports structured data exchange, enabling real-time interaction and reliable state management. Examples include sending transactional requests, monitoring response statuses, and handling JSON-encoded data streams.
